1
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:40,150
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:43,220
[Episode 32]

3
00:01:43,370 --> 00:01:43,810
Keep a close eye

4
00:01:43,810 --> 00:01:44,710
on this person.

5
00:01:45,420 --> 00:01:46,180
Okay, okay.

6
00:01:49,509 --> 00:01:50,210
Han,

7
00:01:50,729 --> 00:01:51,930
report on your work.

8
00:01:55,370 --> 00:01:56,509
As an informant,

9
00:01:56,539 --> 00:01:58,000
I can't do anything useful.

10
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,560
I've really just become a security guard.

11
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:01,620
I'm doing safety training every day.

12
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,380
You haven't gotten into the mine yet?

13
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:05,250
It's tough.

14
00:02:05,830 --> 00:02:07,730
You guys haven't gotten in either.

15
00:02:07,730 --> 00:02:09,860
There are cameras everywhere inside.

16
00:02:09,930 --> 00:02:11,390
How am I supposed to get in?

17
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:14,930
Maybe I should pull out.

18
00:02:24,910 --> 00:02:26,280
Just leave that batch of goods for now.

19
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:28,010
We're not short on them anyway.

20
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:29,510
Talk later.

21
00:02:30,090 --> 00:02:30,590
Okay.

22
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:31,650
Bye-bye.

23
00:02:33,650 --> 00:02:35,050
You can speak Cantonese?

24
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:36,670
Just so-so.

25
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:38,510
Hold on tight.

26
00:02:38,570 --> 00:02:39,070
Okay.

27
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:41,660
Your Cantonese sounds nice.

28
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,610
That's because you haven't heard
a native speaker.

29
00:02:44,610 --> 00:02:46,340
The ones in movies don't count.

30
00:02:46,430 --> 00:02:49,190
Three years, then another 3 years.

31
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:53,190
The farthest place I've ever been

32
00:02:53,190 --> 00:02:54,590
is the provincial capital.

33
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:55,650
For work?

34
00:02:56,130 --> 00:02:57,400
When I just got out,

35
00:02:57,710 --> 00:02:59,579
a friend told me to go clear my head.

36
00:02:59,579 --> 00:03:01,380
I stayed a few days and came back.

37
00:03:03,020 --> 00:03:04,620
I don't like crowded places.

38
00:03:07,740 --> 00:03:09,540
Were there few people in prison?

39
00:03:09,970 --> 00:03:10,710
In prison...

40
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,120
How come I never noticed

41
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:18,570
you talk just like your sister before?

42
00:03:18,579 --> 00:03:19,980
I taught her everything.

43
00:03:23,770 --> 00:03:25,360
The buns are toasted!

44
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:27,100
Come back and eat!

45
00:03:27,230 --> 00:03:27,890
Coming!

46
00:03:29,180 --> 00:03:30,240
We're coming back!

47
00:03:30,950 --> 00:03:31,480
Giddy up!

48
00:03:33,390 --> 00:03:34,970
Aren't you riding pretty well?

49
00:03:34,970 --> 00:03:35,500
Giddy up!

50
00:03:35,530 --> 00:03:36,380
Slow down!

51
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:38,170
Who said I couldn't ride?

52
00:03:38,610 --> 00:03:39,090
Giddy up!

53
00:03:39,090 --> 00:03:39,850
Slow down!

54
00:03:39,870 --> 00:03:40,400
Giddy up!

55
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,120
Here it is.

56
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:51,320
This person

57
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:52,000
left Qinghai

58
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,190
in 2000.

59
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,960
His household registration
is now in Shandong.

60
00:03:57,220 --> 00:03:58,310
Next. Wang Fumin.

61
00:04:00,610 --> 00:04:01,280
Missing.

62
00:04:03,020 --> 00:04:03,910
Bai Ju,

63
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:04,810
where did you

64
00:04:04,810 --> 00:04:05,810
find this information?

65
00:04:05,810 --> 00:04:06,810
It's so detailed.

66
00:04:07,310 --> 00:04:08,770
Why is there Tibetan in it?

67
00:04:09,330 --> 00:04:10,460
I have an informant.

68
00:04:11,990 --> 00:04:13,320
You're full of secrets.

69
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,310
Wang Fumin.

70
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:16,209
Born on March 27,

71
00:04:16,209 --> 00:04:17,829
1953.

72
00:04:18,810 --> 00:04:20,829
Dongxiang County, Tianduo.

73
00:04:22,780 --> 00:04:24,570
He has a son, Wang Jian.

74
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:29,900
This Wang Jian

75
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,500
doesn't have a steady job.

76
00:04:31,540 --> 00:04:32,740
He lives off odd jobs.

77
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:35,050
I don't know if he's in at this hour.

78
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:39,180
This building

79
00:04:39,180 --> 00:04:40,710
is full of migrant workers.

80
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:42,240
Rent is cheap here,

81
00:04:42,659 --> 00:04:44,060
and it's pretty chaotic.

82
00:04:48,550 --> 00:04:49,170
Wang Jian.

83
00:04:50,010 --> 00:04:51,610
Tell us everything you know.

84
00:04:51,690 --> 00:04:53,150
Don't hold anything back.

85
00:04:54,110 --> 00:04:54,700
Captain Xie,

86
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:55,240
Captain Bai,

87
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:56,300
I'll head back now.

88
00:04:56,620 --> 00:04:56,909
Okay.

89
00:04:56,909 --> 00:04:58,370
Thanks for your hard work.

90
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,200
Wang Jian.

91
00:05:02,710 --> 00:05:03,510
Relax.

92
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:04,410
We're just here

93
00:05:04,410 --> 00:05:06,070
to understand the situation.

94
00:05:06,470 --> 00:05:07,270
Don't bother.

95
00:05:08,340 --> 00:05:09,140
Well, this...

96
00:05:10,790 --> 00:05:11,590
Put them here.

97
00:05:13,030 --> 00:05:13,770
Wang Jian,

98
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:15,250
when was the last time

99
00:05:15,270 --> 00:05:16,800
your father contacted you?

100
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:17,920
Well, I...

101
00:05:17,940 --> 00:05:19,400
I don't remember clearly.

102
00:05:19,430 --> 00:05:20,360
I think

103
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,070
it was in 1997.

104
00:05:22,550 --> 00:05:24,330
Not long after he went to South Asia,

105
00:05:24,330 --> 00:05:25,910
he sent back 50,000 yuan.

106
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:28,380
He telegraphed to say

107
00:05:28,380 --> 00:05:29,690
he'd come home after making

108
00:05:29,690 --> 00:05:31,090
big money working there.

109
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:33,180
Where was the telegraph sent from?

110
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:34,540
South Asia.

111
00:05:35,270 --> 00:05:37,480
He sent money back the first 2 years,

112
00:05:37,870 --> 00:05:38,940
but then

113
00:05:38,970 --> 00:05:40,320
we lost contact.

114
00:05:41,650 --> 00:05:42,750
When exactly did he

115
00:05:42,770 --> 00:05:44,030
leave for work in 1997?

116
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:46,210
I think

117
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:47,940
it was autumn.

118
00:05:48,310 --> 00:05:49,040
Autumn.

119
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:52,320
So, all these years,

120
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:54,170
you never looked for your father?

121
00:05:54,170 --> 00:05:55,640
Well, I did.

122
00:05:55,810 --> 00:05:56,450
Back then,

123
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:58,140
when the money he sent ran out,

124
00:05:58,159 --> 00:05:59,510
I wanted to find him.

125
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:00,990
But for so many years,

126
00:06:00,990 --> 00:06:02,250
there has been no news.

127
00:06:03,970 --> 00:06:05,060
My uncle

128
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:06,330
even followed the telegraph address

129
00:06:06,330 --> 00:06:07,710
to South Asia once.

130
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:09,950
They said

131
00:06:09,970 --> 00:06:11,630
no such person existed there.

132
00:06:11,810 --> 00:06:13,040
Did your father

133
00:06:13,150 --> 00:06:14,360
go alone that year,

134
00:06:14,740 --> 00:06:16,340
or did he go with companions?

135
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:17,920
He said

136
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:19,470
someone was going with him,

137
00:06:19,590 --> 00:06:21,080
but he didn't say who.

138
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:24,030
He told me not to ask too many questions.

139
00:06:29,050 --> 00:06:30,400
When your father was home,

140
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,730
who was he closest to?

141
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:34,659
Did you meet any of his colleagues
back then?

142
00:06:34,980 --> 00:06:36,500
There was an uncle.

143
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,390
When my dad went on

144
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,510
long-haul drives,

145
00:06:38,530 --> 00:06:39,409
he would come

146
00:06:39,570 --> 00:06:40,690
to check on us

147
00:06:40,710 --> 00:06:41,920
and bring us things.

148
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:42,770
Later on,

149
00:06:42,770 --> 00:06:44,470
after my dad went to South Asia,

150
00:06:44,470 --> 00:06:45,500
that uncle

151
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:46,560
never came again.

152
00:06:47,180 --> 00:06:48,640
What is that uncle's name?

153
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,740
I...

154
00:06:50,370 --> 00:06:51,830
I called him Uncle...

155
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:52,790
Uncle Wu.

156
00:06:52,940 --> 00:06:53,700
Uncle Wu?

157
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:55,240
Which "Wu"?

158
00:06:55,580 --> 00:06:57,280
I don't know.

159
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:59,540
I just called him that as a kid.

160
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,750
I don't know

161
00:07:00,860 --> 00:07:02,460
what his last name really is.

162
00:07:03,010 --> 00:07:03,620
Wang Jian,

163
00:07:04,470 --> 00:07:05,870
take a look at this photo.

164
00:07:08,620 --> 00:07:09,350
Is this him?

165
00:07:13,970 --> 00:07:15,520
But as I recall,

166
00:07:15,770 --> 00:07:18,130
Uncle Wu had thick lips.

167
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,190
I can't remember clearly.

168
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:23,590
It's been too many years.

169
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:24,600
It's okay.

170
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:27,480
Captain Xie.

171
00:07:27,870 --> 00:07:28,730
We've checked.

172
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,500
Wang Fumin does have a cousin.

173
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:32,010
There are entry and exit records

174
00:07:32,010 --> 00:07:33,190
for his trip to South Asia 6 years ago.

175
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:34,250
The timeline matches.

176
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:36,050
It seems Wang Jian wasn't lying.

177
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:37,990
But as for Wang Fumin,

178
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:39,550
there is no passport information

179
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:41,010
or entry and exit records.

180
00:07:42,130 --> 00:07:43,370
Going abroad was expensive.

181
00:07:43,370 --> 00:07:44,130
Given Wang Fumin's

182
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,220
income situation,

183
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:45,950
back then,

184
00:07:46,510 --> 00:07:48,310
he likely smuggled himself out.

185
00:07:48,340 --> 00:07:49,100
The time he left the country

186
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:50,000
highly coincides with the time

187
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,659
Captain Duojie went missing.

188
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:53,120
Now his whereabouts are unknown,

189
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:55,520
so he's probably fled to avoid punishment.

190
00:07:55,810 --> 00:07:56,430
Fan.

191
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,570
Check against

192
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,430
the list from Hongyuan Freight Company

193
00:08:00,430 --> 00:08:01,010
to see

194
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,370
if there was an employee

195
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,500
surnamed Wu
with the falling-rising tone back then.

196
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:03,890
Okay.

197
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,330
Which Wu?

198
00:08:05,830 --> 00:08:07,150
How many Wus can there be?

199
00:08:07,150 --> 00:08:08,390
Just check them all.

200
00:08:10,130 --> 00:08:10,870
Got it, Captain Bai.

201
00:08:10,870 --> 00:08:11,670
Just a moment.

202
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:12,570
Hurry up.

203
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:18,560
Captain Bai,

204
00:08:18,620 --> 00:08:19,360
found it.

205
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:20,530
No one's surname is Wu
with the falling-rising tone,

206
00:08:20,530 --> 00:08:21,640
but there's only one

207
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:22,840
with the rising tone,

208
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:23,670
Wu Jiang.

209
00:08:31,430 --> 00:08:32,740
Are you blind?

210
00:08:33,340 --> 00:08:35,080
Who are you talking to, you old geezer?

211
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,210
What did you call me?

212
00:08:37,409 --> 00:08:38,270
Getting old,

213
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:40,030
eyes dim, legs weak,

214
00:08:40,110 --> 00:08:41,510
and hard of hearing, too!

215
00:08:41,580 --> 00:08:42,870
Old geezer!

216
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:52,700
Security!

217
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:53,830
Make way! Security!

218
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:57,770
Stop fighting!

219
00:08:58,920 --> 00:08:59,780
Stop fighting!

220
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:01,370
Calm down, Mr. Wu!

221
00:09:01,370 --> 00:09:02,170
You just wait!

222
00:09:03,030 --> 00:09:04,480
Don't run, you brat!

223
00:09:04,670 --> 00:09:05,740
Don't run, you brat!

224
00:09:05,740 --> 00:09:06,550
You just wait!

225
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,050
Mr. Wu, Mr. Wu, you're bleeding!

226
00:09:08,050 --> 00:09:09,070
Help stop the bleeding, quick!

227
00:09:09,070 --> 00:09:09,980
Hurry, hurry!

228
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:10,690
Stop the bleeding now!

229
00:09:10,690 --> 00:09:11,360
Get lost!

230
00:09:11,940 --> 00:09:12,960
Mr. Wu! Mr. Wu!

231
00:09:13,050 --> 00:09:13,820
It's fine, everyone.

232
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:15,080
Just a small misunderstanding.

233
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:15,670
Small misunderstanding.

234
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:16,290
It's okay. It's okay.

235
00:09:16,290 --> 00:09:18,150
Tell everyone to keep having fun.

236
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:37,910
Murder!

237
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:39,000
Still tough?

238
00:09:39,110 --> 00:09:39,660
Get up!

239
00:09:40,130 --> 00:09:40,600
Get up!

240
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:41,820
Murder!

241
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:43,870
Murder!

242
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:45,130
Murder!

243
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,180
Police!

244
00:09:46,370 --> 00:09:47,150
Murder!

245
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:47,820
Freeze!

246
00:09:48,650 --> 00:09:49,300
Stay right there!

247
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:49,840
Freeze!

248
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:51,050
Stand back!

249
00:09:51,580 --> 00:09:52,510
He's a murderer!

250
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:53,540
Murder!

251
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:54,320
Officer,

252
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:55,840
he hit me first.

253
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:56,720
H-He tried to kill me!

254
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,530
He tried to kill me!

255
00:09:57,530 --> 00:09:58,790
Look at what he did to me.

256
00:09:58,790 --> 00:09:59,890
That doesn't mean you can beat him

257
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:00,510
with a baseball bat.

258
00:10:00,510 --> 00:10:01,080
Don't move!

259
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:01,980
Stay right there!

260
00:10:01,980 --> 00:10:02,320
I... I...

261
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,980
I was just trying to scare him.

262
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:04,980
Are you okay?

263
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:05,700
Can you get up?

264
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:06,030
I'm not okay.

265
00:10:06,030 --> 00:10:06,790
I can't get up.

266
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:07,200
I can't get up.

267
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:07,670
Officer,

268
00:10:07,670 --> 00:10:08,750
he's faking it.

269
00:10:08,860 --> 00:10:09,770
I didn't really hurt him.

270
00:10:09,770 --> 00:10:10,460
Quiet.

271
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:11,580
I'll call the police next time.

272
00:10:11,580 --> 00:10:12,480
Definitely call the police.

273
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:14,480
Now you think of calling the police?

274
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:16,350
Do you need to go to the hospital?

275
00:10:19,850 --> 00:10:20,580
Can you stand?

276
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:21,380
I can't get up.

277
00:10:21,620 --> 00:10:22,680
Where are you hurt?

278
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:23,980
My lungs.

279
00:10:24,580 --> 00:10:25,270
Get up first.

280
00:10:25,270 --> 00:10:26,370
Don't touch me. Don't touch me.

281
00:10:26,370 --> 00:10:27,370
Don't touch me. Don't touch me.

282
00:10:27,370 --> 00:10:28,430
Don't touch me. Don't touch me.

283
00:10:28,430 --> 00:10:29,890
Don't hit me. Don't hit me.

284
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:30,790
Call an ambulance first.

285
00:10:30,790 --> 00:10:31,250
Don't hit me.

286
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:32,250
Are you okay, Bro?

287
00:10:33,410 --> 00:10:34,930
Call an ambulance, hurry.

288
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:36,000
You, get up.

289
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:36,500
Mr. Wu.

290
00:10:37,650 --> 00:10:38,340
Come here for a second.

291
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:39,140
What's wrong?

292
00:10:41,340 --> 00:10:42,070
Officer Bai.

293
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:43,800
My trunk is a mess.

294
00:10:44,190 --> 00:10:45,190
Sorry about that.

295
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:46,640
This is all your stuff,

296
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:47,170
isn't it?

297
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:48,790
Yes.

298
00:10:53,340 --> 00:10:54,850
This is a controlled knife.

299
